FBIS4-62737 "drsov095_t_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-095 Daily Report 13 May 1994 BALTIC STATES Estonia Foreign Minister Signs Human Rights Convention 11 May Foreign Minister Signs Human Rights Convention 11 May WS1605113094 Tallinn ETA in English 1611 GMT 13 May 94 WS1605113094 Tallinn ETA English BFN ["News Release"] [Text] Estonian Foreign Minister Juri Luik signed, together with Council of Europe member states foreign ministers, in Strasbourg, on Wednesday [11 May], European Human Rights Convention 11th protocol, spokeswoman of the Ministry Mari-Ann Rikken told a press conference on Friday [13 May]. The protocol prescribes foundation of a permanent European Human Rights Court, which would receive complaints from persons, groups of persons, non-governmental organisations and states. The Court includes one judge, elected for six years, from each Council of Europe member state. The protocol comes into force after ratification. Estonia, however, has to ratify the convention and its first 10 protocols first.
